content.body:
read lesson three and decide if the sentences are true or false. Click the correct answer.

  • My first lesson is French today. True - false
  • Mrs Green is standing in the doorway. True - false
  • He is saying good morning to us. True - false
  • Everybody is here. True - false
  • We have got our school diaries. True - false -
  • Mr Green is proud of us. True - false
  • In this period we are talking about all the food that we take to school. True - false
  • Naomi has got crayons and a an eraser. True - false
  • Peter has got an eraser and a pencil. True - false
  • Peter has got a pencase. True - false
  • Mr Green gives him a pencil. True - false
  • The girl next to Emma has a pencase, some books and some notebooks on her table. True - false
  • Emma's is right. True - false
  • When Mr Green is walking to his desk, Martin is talking. True - false
  • Martin is looking for Emma's calculator. True - false
  • The calculator is on the floor. True - false
  • There is something on Mr Green's desk. True - false
  • Anna can't answer Mr Green's question. True - false
  • There's a stapler on Mr Green's desk. True - false
  • The children have got staplers too. True - false
  • Mark sees scissors. True - false
  • The children must write down all the school items that they have got in the classroom. True - false
